---
title: contrai CLI — screen flow (RichView)
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    [*] --> Landing : uv run contrai

    Landing : <b>0. Landing</b><br/>target-score picker<br/>(500 / 1000 / 1500 / 2000 / 3000)
    Bidding : <b>1. Bidding</b><br/>request_bid_action(player, history)<br/>"80 h" / "pass" / "double" / "redouble"
    MidTrick : <b>2. Mid-trick</b><br/>request_card_action(player, trick, contract, playable)<br/>diamond + live-winner gold pill
    TrickWon : <b>3. Trick won</b><br/>on_trick_complete(trick, winner, round)<br/>"Press [Enter] to continue…"
    EndGame : <b>4. End game</b><br/>show_end_game(status)<br/>[n] new · [r] rematch · [q] quit

    Landing --> Bidding : Enter
    Bidding --> Bidding : AI bids,<br/>still bidding
    Bidding --> Landing : all 4 pass<br/>(redeal)
    Bidding --> MidTrick : contract set,<br/>play_all_tricks starts
    MidTrick --> TrickWon : 4th card played,<br/>Round fires hook
    TrickWon --> MidTrick : next trick<br/>(round not done)
    TrickWon --> Bidding : 8 tricks done,<br/>round scored,<br/>target not reached
    TrickWon --> EndGame : 8 tricks done,<br/>round scored,<br/>check_game_over true

    EndGame --> Landing : [n] new game<br/>(fresh target prompt)
    EndGame --> Bidding : [r] rematch<br/>(same target)
    EndGame --> [*] : [q] quit

    note right of MidTrick
        Hand row: green pill for legal plays,
        dim for illegal. Hint line below
        explains the constraint
        ("must follow ♠" / "must trump — W led K♣"
        / "free discard").
    end note

    note right of TrickWon
        Round.play_trick calls
        view.on_trick_complete(...) only if
        hasattr(view, "on_trick_complete").
        Non-Rich callers are unaffected.
    end note

